0                                   1190              *        Note: In The following comments, SEND and RECEIVE refer to
                                    1191              *        communicating with the VTAM application - VTAM macros are
                                    1192              *        used.  --  READ and WRITE refer to communicating with the
                                    1193              *        ASCII terminal - TSEG macros are used.
                                    1194              *
                                    1195              *        OUTBOUND indicates data flow from the IBM Application
                                    1196              *        (VTAM RECEIVE)- to This Module - to MILTEN (TSEG WRITE)
                                    1197              *        - to the User Terminal.
                                    1198              *
                                    1199              *        INBOUND indicates data flow from the User Terminal -
                                    1200              *        from MILTEN (READ) - to This Module - to the IBM APPLICATION
                                    1201              *        - (VTAM SEND).
                                    1202              *
                                    1203              *        Representative APPL definition statements are:
                                    1204              *
                                    1205              *        A070   APPL AUTH=ACQ,EAS=2,VPACING=2,MODETAB=S3278,SESSLIM=YES
                                    1206              *        A071   APPL AUTH=ACQ,EAS=2,VPACING=2,MODETAB=S3278,SESSLIM=YES
                                    1207              *        A072   APPL AUTH=ACQ,EAS=2,VPACING=2,MODETAB=S3278,SESSLIM=YES
                                    1208              *        A073   APPL AUTH=ACQ,EAS=2,VPACING=2,MODETAB=S3278,SESSLIM=YES
                                    1209              *
                                    1210              *        The "SESSLIM=YES" parameter is not required, but recommended.
                                    1211              *
                                    1212              *        Note that the same Mode Table is used as with real terminals.
                                    1213              *
                                    1214              *        The following non-standard Stanford AID codes are used
                                    1215              *
                                    1216              *            AID     ESC Seq    Meaning
                                    1217              *
                                    1218              *            67      ESC-C      Clear-Screen
                                    1219              *            65      ESC-A      ATTN
                                    1220              *            83      ESC-S      PA1

                                   13478  1           *
                                   13479  1           *  Screen image:
                                   13480  1           *     Each character that is to be displayed on the screen has
                                   13481  1           *     information in each of the following buffers. These buffers
                                   13482  1           *     are maintained in 3270 format.
                                   13483  1           *
                                   13484  1           *     Field attribute characters (FAC) are stored as text.  They are
1VETS     (VETS2025) (12:59) (15MAR04) LOCAL CONTROL BLOCKS                                      VTWA                       Page   10
0Current Usings:  (CP,R11) (CV,R12)
0D-Loc  Object Code    Addr1 Addr2  Stmt Lv Lineno    Source Statement           (Hibal 5, Asmedit 3.3)  HLASM R4.0  2004/03/15 12.59
+_____  ______ ____    _____ _____  ____ __ ______    ______ _________
0                                  13485  1           *     identified as being less than X'40', but not Null (X'00').
                                   13486  1           *     The X'02' bit (Reserved in IBM's definition) is turned on
                                   13487  1           *     when any FAC is stored, so that a X'00' FAC will not appear as
                                   13488  1           *     a character "NULL".
                                   13489  1           *
                                   13490  1           *   Because the Wylbur Model Terminal does not distinguish between
                                   13491  1           *     NULL (X'00') and SPace (X'40'), NULLs will be changed to SPaces
                                   13492  1           *     when data is read from the ASCII terminal, and trailing SPaces
                                   13493  1           *     (in addition to NULLs) will be stripped from incoming fields.
                                   13494  1           *
 000094                            13495  1           VTWTEXTP   DS    A                   Screen Text PTR
 000098                            13496  1           VTWHIP     DS    A                   Screen Highlight PTR
 00009C                            13497  1           VTWCOLP    DS    A                   Screen Color PTR
 0000A0                            13498  1           VTWCSP     DS    A                   Screen Character Set
 0000A4                000A4 000A4 13499                       END

                                   13584              **  SETVOPT -- SET VOPTIONS Command.
                                   13585              *
                                   13586              *  SET VOPT [terminal_name[,number]] [,{ON|OFF}]
                                   13587              *
                                   13588              *  "terminal_name" omitted enables|disables entire interface
                                   13589              *  "number" indicates number of consecutive terminals
                                   13590              *  "number" omitted defines only one terminal
                                   13591              *  "ON" (default) defines and enables the terminals or interface
                                   13592              *  "OFF" defines and disables the terminals or interface
                                   13593              *

0                                  15645              *
                                   15646              **  NEXTNAME -- Routine to return the next name of a terminal when
                                   15647              **              the first name and binary count are known.
                                   15648              **
                                   15649              *
                                   15650              **    On entry:
                                   15651              **      R0 = L'name for initial call
                                   15652              **      R0 = 0 for sucessive calls
                                   15653              **      R1 = @name for initial call
                                   15654              **      r2 = 0 for only 1 terminal
                                   15655              **      r2 = binary number of sucessive terminals
                                   15656              *
                                   15657              **    On exit:
                                   15658              **      R1 = @name of terminal, 8 characters blank filled
                                   15659              **      R0 = 0 indicates all applicable names have been delivered
                                   15660              **
                                   15661              ** Note: Trailing digits in the name are incremented, until the number
                                   15662              **       has been satisfied, or until all digits are "9".
                                   15663              **       The initialization call will always return the name entered,
                                   15664              **       with trailing spaces.
                                   15665              *
0                                  15667              *
                                   15668              **    REGISTER USE FOR THIS ROUTINE:
                                   15669              **       R2 = NUMBER OF TERMINALS (INITIAL CALL ONLY)
                                   15670              **       R3 = WORK
                                   15671              **       R4 = INDEX
                                   15672              **       R5 = INDEX LIMIT
                                   15673              **       R6 =
                                   15674              *

0                                  16592              *
                                   16593              **   LOGON -- Routine to process the VLOGON command.  Called in order
                                   16594              **            to obtain a work area.
                                   16595              **
                                   16596              **    On entry:
                                   16597              **      logon parameters to be obtained.
                                   16598              **
                                   16599              **    On exit:
                                   16600              **      R6 = @VTWA returned.
                                   16601              **      VLOGON control blocks have been obtained
                                   16602              **      and session has been requested.  The next
                                   16603              **      expected activity is the receipt of a BIND.
                                   16604              *
0000000                00000 00014 16606              LOGONWA  RECORD BEGIN              WORK AREA
 000000                            16614  1           MODENL     DS    F                   LENGTH OF LOGMODE_NAME
 000004                            16615  1           MODEN      DS    CL8                 LOGMODE_NAME
 00000C                            16616  1           UDATAL     DS    F                   LENGTH OF USER_DATA
 000010                            16617  1           UDATA      DS    A                   @ USER_DATA
 000014                00014 00014 16618                       END
0                                  16628              *
                                   16629              **    REGISTER USE FOR THIS ROUTINE:
                                   16630              **       R2 =
                                   16631              **       R3 = RPL
                                   16632              **       R4 = NIB
                                   16633              **       R5 = ACB
                                   16634              **       R6 = VTWA
                                   16635              *

0                                  19718              *
                                   19719              **  MAINLINE -- This is the main processing loop.  It receives
                                   19720              **              commands from the host application, and causes them
                                   19721              **              to be executed.  This generally involves reading
                                   19722              **              and writing to the terminal.
                                   19723              **
                                   19724              *
                                   19725              **    ENTRY is by BRANCH to MAINLINE or MAINLINE1 from the WYLBUR
                                   19726              **    command routines VLOGON, VLOGOFF, VGO, and VATTN
                                   19727              **
                                   19728              **      BR = @ MAINLINE
                                   19729              *
                                   19730              **    Exit is by BRANCH to CVNEXT, and is made within proc

                                   21107              **  PROCRCVC -- Routine to process the completion of a data RECEIVE

                                   21114              **      VTWORUC POINTS TO THE OUTBOUND BUFFER CHAIN
                                   21115              **      R6 = @ VTWA

+___    ______ ____    _____ _____  ____ __ ______    ______ _________
0                                  31261              *
                                   31262              **  PRCESSCR -- Routine to process received buffer updates
                                   31263              **            from the  Application, and update the 3270 buffer image.
                                   31264              **
                                   31265              **    On entry:
                                   31266              **      VTWOBRUC points to the first buffer header
                                   31267              **      R1 = Offset in data to start processing
                                   31268              **      R0 = 0 Start processing with first buffer
                                   31269              **      R0 = @ Buffer to start processing structure
                                   31270              **
                                   31271              **    On exit: R15 = 0 or contains error sense code
                                   31272              **             R0  = @ current beffer
                                   31273              **             R0  = 0 if entire buffer was screen data
                                   31274              **             R1  = Data offset of non screen structured field
                                   31275              **                   or offset of X'70' for RENEX Transparent Data
                                   31276              **    The following indicates that additional proceessing must be done:
                                   31277              **       R0 ~= 0      Indicates non screen output to be done
                                   31278              **       VTWRCMD ~= 0 Indicates a READ command to be processed
                                   31279              **       VTWFRNXT ON  Indicates RENEX transparency mode
                                   31280              **
                                   31281              ** => Note: This routine may be called from the Receive Dispatcher
                                   31282              **          Routine, so that the screen image may be updated
                                   31283              **          while the user is NOT active. <=
                                   31284              *
0000000                00000 0000E 31286              PRCSWA   RECORD BEGIN             WORK AREA
 000000                            31294  1           PRCSSCRF   DS    F                   FULL WORD SCRATCH AREA
 000004                            31295  1           PRCSFLEN   DS    F                   STRUCTURED FIELD LENGTH
 000008                            31296  1           RCVPAIRC   DS    H                   SFE, SA, MF PAIR COUNT
 00000A                            31297  1           RCVCAHI    DS    X                   CHARACTER HIGHLIGHT
 00000B                            31298  1           RCVCACOL   DS    X                   CHARACTER COLOR
 00000C                            31299  1           RCVCACS    DS    X                   CHARACTER CHARACTER SET
 00000D 00                         31300  1           PRCSFLA    FLAG  ,                   FLAGS
 PRCSFLA.LASTFACP  80 ONES         31304  1                      FLAG  LASTFACP             LAST FAC WAS PROTECTED
 PRCSFLA.GESC      40 ONES         31309  1                      FLAG  GESC                 NEXT CHARACTER FROM F1 SET
 PRCSFLA.PTEN      20 ONES         31314  1                      FLAG  PTEN                 PROGRAM TAB ORDER ENTERS NULLS
 00000E                0000E 0000E 31319                       END
0                                  31329              *
                                   31330              **    REGISTER USE FOR THIS ROUTINE:
                                   31331              **       R2 = CHARACTER BEING PROCESSED
                                   31332              **       R3 = SCREEN CURRENT INDEX
                                   31333              **       R4 = INPUT BUFFER DATA INDEX
                                   31334              **       R5 = INPUT BUFFER ADDRESS
                                   31335              **       R6 = VTWA
                                   31336              *

0                                  35619              *
                                   35620              ** FINDNFAC - Routine to find the next Field Attribute
                                   35621              **            Character in the 3270 buffer image.
                                   35622              **
                                   35623              **    On entry:
                                   35624              **      R1 = current buffer index
                                   35625              **      R6 = @VTWA
                                   35626              **      VTWTEXTP = pointer to screen buffer
                                   35627              **      VTWBUFL  = Buffer Length
                                   35628              **
                                   35629              **    On exit: R1  = -1 If no FAC is encountered before end of buffer.
                                   35630              **             R1  = Buffer Index of next FAC character. If R1 points
                                   35631              **                   to a FAC on input, R1 is not changed.
                                   35632              **             CC  = (EQ) If Found, (NE) If Not Found
                                   35633              *
0                                  35635              *
                                   35636              **    REGISTER USE FOR THIS ROUTINE:
                                   35637              **       R1 = BUFFER INDEX
                                   35638              **       R2 = BUFFER CHARACTER
                                   35639              **       R3 =
                                   35640              **       R4 = BUFFER LENGTH
                                   35641              **       R5 = @BUFFER
                                   35642              **       R6 = VTWA
                                   35643              *
0004892 50E0 D000/9008_      00000 35645              FINDNFAC PROC  ,                   FIND THE NEXT FAC

0                                  35936              *
                                   35937              ** REPEATOA - Routine to Repeat To Address - place multiple instances
                                   35938              **            of a Character in the 3270 buffer image, including
                                   35939              **            attributes. This routine stops at the end of the buffer,
                                   35940              **            it will NOT wrap.
                                   35941              **
                                   35942              **    On entry:
                                   35943              **      R0 = Character to store, and Attributes as:
                                   35944              **           CS|COL|HI|Text
                                   35945              **      R1 = Ending Buffer Index +1
                                   35946              **      R3 = Current Buffer Index
                                   35947              **      R6 = @VTWA
                                   35948              **      VTWTEXTP etc = pointer to screen buffer
                                   35949              **      VTWBUFL  = Buffer Length
                                   35950              **
                                   35951              **    On exit: CC  = (EQ) If Performed, (NE) If No characters placed
                                   35952              *
0                                  35954              *
                                   35955              **    REGISTER USE FOR THIS ROUTINE:
                                   35956              **       R0 = CHARACTER TO INSERT (FROM ENTRY)
                                   35957              **       R1 = ENDING BUFFER INDEX+1 FROM ENTRY)
                                   35958              **       R2 = WORKING BUFFER INDEX
                                   35959              **       R3 = CURRENT BUFFER INDEX (FROM ENTRY)
                                   35960              **       R4 = BUFFER LENGTH
                                   35961              **       R5 = @BUFFER
                                   35962              **       R6 = VTWA
                                   35963              *

0                                  36200              *
                                   36201              **  SENDSCR -- Routine to send 3270 buffer image to the application.
                                   36202              **
                                   36203              **  Note: Orders and data from partition zero, are never transmitted
                                   36204              **        as a structured field.
                                   36205              **
                                   36206              **    On entry:
                                   36207              **      VTWTEXTP = @ 3270 screen buffer
                                   36208              **      VTWBUFL  = length of above
                                   36209              **      VTWICPOS = current insert cursor buffer position
                                   36210              **      VTWRCMD  = read command received (zero if none)
                                   36211              **      RS3270   = the hardware Read State
                                   36212              **      AID3270  = AID received
                                   36213              **      VTWRMODE = Reply Mode (1,2,or 3)
                                   36214              **
                                   36215              **    On exit: R15 = 0 or points to error message.

0                                  37947              *
                                   37948              **  SENDQR -- Routine to format and send Query Responses to the
                                   37949              **            Application
                                   37950              **
                                   37951              **    On entry:
                                   37952              **      VTWQLIST = list of replies to be sent
                                   37953              **
                                   37954              **    On exit: R15 = 0 or points to error message.
                                   37955              **             Terminal Read State set to Retry Read
                                   37956              *
                                   37957              *
                                   37958              **    REGISTER USE FOR THIS ROUTINE:
                                   37959              **       R2 =
                                   37960              **       R3 = VTWQLIST INDEX
                                   37961              **       R4 = OUTPUT BUFFER DATA INDEX
                                   37962              **       R5 = OUTPUT BUFFER ADDRESS
                                   37963              **       R6 = VTWA
                                   37964              *
0                                  37966                       MACRO
                                   37967                       CHECKSPA ,                CHECK SPACE AND STEP TO NEXT BUFFER
                                   37968                       IF    (R1,GE,VTBDLENG),BEGIN
                                   37969                       STH   R4,VTBCOUNT
                                   37970                       L     R4,VTWRSIZI                   GET THE NEXT BUFFER
                                   37971                       LA    R0,@R4+VTBDATA-VTBHEAD
                                   37972                       VCALL GETCORE
                                   37973                       ST    R1,VTBNEXT
                                   37974                       LR    R5,R1
                                   37975                       XC    VTBHEAD(VTBDATA-VTBHEAD),VTBHEAD
                                   37976                       MVC   VTBID,=C'VTBH'
                                   37977                       STH   R4,VTBDLENG
                                   37978                       CLEAR R4
                                   37979                       END
                                   37980                       MEND

                                   38889  1 01-ISTBL +BLELMPEO   EQU   B'11000000'             LMPEO CONTROL FLAGS --
                                   38890  1          +*                                      RESERVED UNLESS OPTCD=LMPEO
                                   38891  1 01-ISTBL +BLEBEGRU   EQU   B'10000000'             THIS ENTRY BEGINS AN RU --
                                   38892  1          +*                                      VTAM MAY NOT BREAK UP THE RU

                                   38895  1          +*                                      BUFFER LIST ENTRY) TO BREAK UP
                                   38896  1          +*                                      THE NEXT SET OF DATA UNLESS

                                   38898  1          +*                                      PRECLUDES IT
                                   38899  1          +*        EQU   B'00111111'             RESERVED - NOT AVAILABLE

0                                  48784              *
                                   48785              **  DRCVE -- Asynchronous routine to process normal flow receive
                                   48786              **           completions, from the application.  If user is
                                   48787              **           NOT active, updates the 3270 screen image.
                                   48788              **
